        day: 5, refs: ['Psalm 90', 'Psalm 91', 'Psalm 121'],
        dayTitle: 'Day 5 · Refuge',
        keyVerse: { ref: 'Psalm 91:1-2', text: 'He who dwells in the shelter of the Most High will abide in the shadow of the Almighty. I will say to the LORD, "My refuge and my fortress, my God, in whom I trust."' },
        devotional: 'Psalm 90 is Moses\'s psalm — God as our dwelling place from generation to generation. Psalm 91 is the deepest "refuge" psalm — He will cover you with His feathers, deliver you from the snare, send angels concerning you. Psalm 121 is the pilgrim\'s song — I lift my eyes to the hills; my help comes from the LORD.\n\nThe theme is REFUGE. A place to hide. A fortress. A shelter. A shadow. A roof in the storm. Wings to crawl under. The Bible uses every available metaphor to make the same point — God is a SAFE PLACE.\n\nWhat are you RUNNING FROM today? Probably something specific. The diagnosis. The conversation. The future. The accusation in your head. The shame. The world is asking you to handle it alone. The psalms invite you under wings. Today, find a quiet moment. Picture the shelter. Crawl in. Stay longer than feels productive. The refuge is real.',
        prompt: 'God as refuge. What are you running from?',
