        day: 8, refs: ['Psalm 12', 'Psalm 13', 'Psalm 14'],
        dayTitle: 'Day 8 · "How Long, O Lord?"',
        keyVerse: { ref: 'Psalm 13:1', text: 'How long, O LORD? Will you forget me forever? How long will you hide your face from me?' },
        devotional: 'Psalm 13 asks "HOW LONG?" four times in two verses. David is not whispering. He is yelling at God IN GOD\'S DIRECTION. That is the bravest possible kind of faith — the faith that says "I am not leaving the conversation, but I am not pretending either."\n\nAnd then, in verse 5, something turns. "BUT I have trusted in Your steadfast love." Both can be true on the same page. The how-long question AND the trust statement. The psalm holds them together without resolving the tension.\n\nPray "how long" about something specific today. Out loud if you can. Find a private place and ask God directly. "How long will this depression last?" "How long until that diagnosis turns?" "How long until that relationship reconciles?" "How long until my parents stop fighting?" Bring the question. Then sit with His "but" — His steadfast love that does not budge regardless of how long the answer takes.',
        prompt: '"How long, O Lord?" — pray it about something specific.',
