        day: 13, refs: ['Psalm 28', 'Psalm 29', 'Psalm 30'],
        dayTitle: 'Day 13 · Joy Comes in the Morning',
        keyVerse: { ref: 'Psalm 30:5', text: 'For his anger is but for a moment, and his favor is for a lifetime. Weeping may tarry for the night, but joy comes with the morning.' },
        devotional: 'Psalm 30 contains one of the most quoted lines about suffering and recovery. "WEEPING MAY TARRY FOR THE NIGHT, BUT JOY COMES WITH THE MORNING." David is not promising the night will be short. He is promising the morning will come.\n\nThat is not the same as denial. The night is real. The weeping is real. The pain is not minimized. The psalm acknowledges that grief can SLEEP OVER — it can stay the night. But it cannot stay forever. Morning is coming. And the joy that comes with the morning is from the same hand that allowed the night.\n\nWhat NIGHT are you in? Probably one specific season. The grief. The depression. The hard chapter. The waiting. The long winter. Psalm 30 does not promise it will be over by Tuesday. It promises MORNING IS COMING. The God who promises that has the track record to back it up. Hold on. The dawn has a different feel than the dark.',
