        devotional: 'Psalm 46 is one of the noisiest poems in the Bible. Mountains falling into the sea. Waters roaring. Nations raging. Right in the middle of all that chaos, God says one phrase: BE STILL, AND KNOW THAT I AM GOD.\n\nThe Hebrew is closer to "stop striving" or "let your hands fall." It is not a command to FEEL peaceful. It is a command to STOP gripping. To unclench. To set down whatever you have been white-knuckling. The stillness is the precondition for the knowing.\n\nTake 60 SECONDS of literal stillness right now. Put a timer on it. No prayer. No analysis. No solving. Just being. Drop the shoulders. Unclench the jaw. Take a breath all the way down. Let your hands fall. KNOW that He is God. He is exalted among the nations. He is exalted in the earth. He does not need your help to be God today.',
