        devotional: 'Psalm 47 is a coronation psalm. GOD IS THE KING OF ALL THE EARTH. The nations are HIS — not just Israel\'s, not just the church\'s. All of it. Every culture, every language, every demographic, every voting bloc, every neighborhood — His.\n\nThat detail should reorient your political anxiety. Whatever empire you are watching with concern, whatever leader you are panicking about, whatever election outcome you are dreading — the actual King is already on the actual throne. You are not waiting for Him to ascend. He never abdicated.\n\nWhere are YOU trying to be king? Probably some specific area. The relationship you are managing. The future you are scripting. The reputation you are protecting. The household you are running with too much control. The Christian who treats God as King in church and themselves as king Monday through Saturday has not yet fully received the Psalm 47 verdict. Step down today. He has been the King the whole time.',
