        devotional: 'Psalm 54 is a short, urgent psalm. David wrote it when the Ziphites betrayed him to Saul. In the middle of being hunted by his own countrymen, David anchors his prayer in one declarative sentence: "BEHOLD, GOD IS MY HELPER. The Lord is the upholder of my life."\n\nThat is the move of trained faith. When help seems absent from human sources, David turns his eyes upward and ANNOUNCES that help is still available. Not "I hope God will help." "GOD IS my helper." Present tense. Already true.\n\nWhere is help most NEEDED this week? Be specific. The job hunt. The medical situation. The relationship that is on the rocks. The wayward kid. The financial pinch. The grief. Psalm 54 invites you to make David\'s declaration over your own situation. Not as denial of the difficulty — as a refusal to let the difficulty have the last word. Behold, God is your helper this week. The upholder of your life.',
