        dayTitle: 'Day 20 · Cast Your Cares',
        keyVerse: { ref: 'Psalm 55:22', text: 'Cast your burden on the LORD, and he will sustain you; he will never permit the righteous to be moved.' },
        devotional: 'Psalm 55:22 gives the same instruction Peter quotes in 1 Peter 5:7. CAST YOUR BURDEN on the Lord. Cast is a fishing word — to hurl with weight behind it. Not "set it gently down." HURL it. Refuse to carry it any more.\n\nThe Hebrew word for "burden" can also mean "lot" or "what is given to you." Whatever has been given to you that is too heavy — cast it. The Lord will SUSTAIN you. The verb means to bear up under, to support, to feed. The same God who gave you the gift of breath sustains you under the weight of whatever you are carrying.\n\nCast ONE specific care right now. Not in theory. Out loud, in prayer. "Lord, I am casting this on You — the [thing]. I refuse to carry it alone any longer. You sustain me under it." Say the words. Hurl the burden. Some of those burdens come back the next morning. Cast them again. The Christian life is a hundred castings over a lifetime.',
        prompt: '"Cast your cares on the Lord." Cast one specific care right now.',
