        day: 21, refs: ['Psalm 62', 'Psalm 63', 'Psalm 65'],
        dayTitle: 'Day 21 · My Soul Thirsts',
        keyVerse: { ref: 'Psalm 63:1', text: 'O God, you are my God; earnestly I seek you; my soul thirsts for you; my flesh faints for you, as in a dry and weary land where there is no water.' },
        devotional: 'Psalm 63 is David in the wilderness of Judah. Physically dry. Spiritually parched. And he turns his thirst toward God — "my soul thirsts for YOU." He is not trying to ignore the thirst. He is naming the OBJECT of it.\n\nThat is a discipline most modern Christians never develop. We have been trained to satisfy thirst with anything within reach. The phone. The shopping cart. The next show. The relationship. The drink. The food. The compliment. All of those address surface thirst. None of them address the deeper one — the spiritual thirst that David names. The soul wants GOD, not just relief.\n\nWhat are you thirsty FOR INSTEAD of God right now? Honest answer. Most of us can name it. The numb. The distraction. The approval. The escape. Today, redirect the thirst. Name it. "I am thirsty. I have been trying to satisfy it with — but my soul actually wants You." Then go to the well that does not run dry. He is the spring David was reaching for.',
        prompt: '"My soul thirsts for You." What are you thirsty for instead?',
