        day: 22, refs: ['Psalm 66', 'Psalm 67', 'Psalm 68'],
        dayTitle: 'Day 22 · Praise and Blessing',
        keyVerse: { ref: 'Psalm 67:1-2', text: 'May God be gracious to us and bless us and make his face to shine upon us, that your way may be known on earth, your saving power among all nations.' },
        devotional: 'Psalm 67 is short and brilliant. It opens with a request for blessing. "MAY GOD BE GRACIOUS to us and BLESS us and make HIS FACE TO SHINE upon us." Sounds nice. But notice the PURPOSE clause in v. 2: "THAT Your way may be known on earth, Your saving power among all nations."\n\nGod\'s blessing is not just for the comfort of His people. It is for the EVANGELISM of the world. The blessing flows in so that it can flow out. You are blessed to be a blessing. Your prosperity, your joy, your peace, your stability — those are God\'s tools for getting His way known on the earth.\n\nWrite a single sentence of THANKS today. Just one. Specific. Real. "Thank You, God, for ___." Then ask yourself: how is the blessing I just named meant to flow OUT? To whom? Through what action? The thanksgiving discipline is meant to spill over into generosity. Receive the blessing. Then move it.',
