        devotional: 'ADONAI means LORD, MASTER, RULER. It is the title of someone who has authority — and it is the title every Christian uses when calling Jesus LORD. Psalm 8 stacks the words on purpose: "O LORD (YHWH), our Lord (ADONAI)" — the covenant God who also reigns as Master.\n\nCalling someone "Lord" in the ancient world meant SUBMISSION. It meant their will outranked yours. You served at their pleasure. You obeyed when they spoke. Most modern Christians use the word LORD as a religious title with very little of that bite. We say "Jesus is Lord" and then live as if our preferences are still the deciding vote.\n\nWho is the master of your MINUTES today? Honest answer. Is it your phone, your career, your appetites, your fear, your reputation? Or ADONAI? The first lord of your day is the one who actually has you. Pick again today.',
