        dayTitle: 'Day 5 · YAHWEH-JIREH — The Lord Will Provide',
        keyVerse: { ref: 'Genesis 22:14', text: 'So Abraham called the name of that place, "The LORD will provide"; as it is said to this day, "On the mount of the LORD it shall be provided."' },
        devotional: 'YAHWEH-JIREH means "the Lord will provide" or "the Lord will see and provide for." Abraham named a mountain after this name on the day God spared Isaac and substituted a ram in his place. The provision arrived AFTER Abraham obeyed — not before. He had to climb the mountain to find out what the provision would be.\n\nThat detail still matters. Most of us want to see the ram in the thicket before we start climbing. Abraham did not get that option. He gathered the wood. He built the altar. He raised the knife. THEN God interrupted with the provision. The act of obedience precedes the revelation of the ram, almost every time.\n\nWhere do you most need that name today? The bill you do not know how to pay. The conversation you do not know how to have. The decision you cannot see the outcome of. Climb the mountain. The provision is on Him. He has been showing up at the top of mountains since Genesis.',
