        keyVerse: { ref: 'Exodus 15:26', text: 'For I am the LORD, your healer.' },
        devotional: 'YAHWEH-RAPHA means THE LORD WHO HEALS. God revealed this name at Marah, where Israel found bitter water and could not drink it. Moses threw a piece of wood into the water and it became sweet. Then God said: I AM YOUR HEALER.\n\nThe Hebrew word RAPHA means more than physical recovery. It means to mend, to repair, to restore, to put right what was broken. God heals bodies. He also heals marriages, friendships, identities, traumas, addictions, generational patterns. Some healings happen quickly. Some take decades. Some He completes only in glory. But the name is His — He is THE HEALER. It is part of His identity.\n\nWhat does healing need to look like in your life right now? Be specific. The body part that has been hurting. The wound from your childhood. The shame loop that keeps running. The marriage that needs mending. Bring it to YAHWEH-RAPHA. He does not flinch at the diagnosis. He is the Healer.',
