        devotional: 'After Israel defeated the Amalekites — while Moses held up his hands and Joshua fought in the valley — Moses built an altar and named it YAHWEH-NISSI. The LORD MY BANNER. In ancient warfare, the banner was the flag a soldier rallied around. It marked the army you belonged to. It was visible from across the battlefield.\n\nGod was not just helping Israel win the battle. He was their banner. Their identity. Their rallying point. Their flag. The battle was won not by Joshua\'s strategy alone, but by Moses keeping the banner raised on the hill.\n\nWhose flag are you flying in your battles? The American flag. The flag of a political party. The flag of a career. The flag of your family\'s expectations. The flag of comfort. Each of those flies somewhere. Today, raise the right banner. YAHWEH-NISSI is the only banner worth giving your life to. The battles look different when you are fighting under His flag.',
