        devotional: 'Gideon was hiding from the Midianites in a winepress, threshing wheat in secret, when an angel of the Lord called him "mighty man of valor." Gideon protested — he was the youngest in the weakest family of the smallest tribe. He was anything but mighty. The Lord spoke peace over him. Gideon built an altar and named it YAHWEH-SHALOM: THE LORD IS PEACE.\n\nShalom in Hebrew means more than the absence of conflict. It means WHOLENESS — every part of you in right relationship with God, with others, with yourself, and with creation. It is the full-bodied flourishing the Bible imagines for human life. Sin shattered shalom. Christ is restoring it. The name reminds us that PEACE is not a circumstance God can give you — He IS peace.\n\nWhere are you most without peace right now? The relationship. The future. The conversation that has not happened. The bank account. Plant the name of YAHWEH-SHALOM there. He goes BEFORE His peace. The peace flows from the Person.',
