        keyVerse: { ref: 'Jeremiah 23:6', text: 'In his days Judah will be saved, and Israel will dwell securely. And this is the name by which he will be called: "The LORD is our righteousness."' },
        devotional: 'YAHWEH-TSIDKENU is one of the most theologically important names in the Old Testament. It means THE LORD OUR RIGHTEOUSNESS. Jeremiah promised it would be the name of the coming Messiah. Paul preaches the fulfillment in Romans — Christ\'s righteousness is IMPUTED to us. Credited. Transferred. Counted as ours.\n\nThat is the gospel in one phrase. The righteousness you stand in before God is not yours. It is HIS. Your record was bad. His was perfect. On the cross there was a swap — He took your sin, you got His righteousness. That swap is permanent and complete the moment you trust Him.\n\nMost Christians believe this in theory and live as if their daily standing with God is still based on their performance. They wake up trying to be righteous enough. YAHWEH-TSIDKENU rules out that pursuit. The righteousness is His, gifted to you, settled forever. Today, rest in it. You are not trying to earn what was already declared true on the cross.',
