        devotional: 'The last verse of Ezekiel ends his vision of the restored Jerusalem with a name. The city will be called YAHWEH-SHAMMAH: THE LORD IS THERE. After all the exile, all the rubble, all the prophecy of judgment, the final word of Ezekiel is that God\'s presence will define His people\'s home.\n\nJesus picks up the same theme at the end of Matthew: "I am with you always, to the end of the age." Wherever His people gather — in Jerusalem, in a basement church in Iran, in a Texas suburb, in a high school cafeteria where two believers eat lunch together — that is where the LORD IS. Geography stopped being a barrier to His presence the moment the Spirit was poured out at Pentecost.\n\nWherever you wake up tomorrow, that is where He is. The hospital room. The college dorm. The empty house. The hard family dinner. YAHWEH-SHAMMAH is the name that says you do not have to travel to find Him. He is THERE. Wherever you are.',
