        devotional: 'YAHWEH-RA\'AH means THE LORD MY SHEPHERD. David — who had been a shepherd as a boy — wrote Psalm 23 as a song of trust in the God who shepherded HIM. The whole psalm is a tour of what a shepherd does. He LEADS. He RESTORES. He COMFORTS. He PREPARES a table. He ANOINTS. He pursues with goodness and mercy.\n\nA shepherd is NOT a farmer. A farmer drives livestock from behind. A shepherd LEADS from the front, walking the same path he asks the sheep to walk. Wherever YAHWEH-RA\'AH is taking you, He has been on that road first. Every valley you are walking, He has walked. Every shadow has fallen over His shoulders before it fell over yours.\n\nRead Psalm 23 slowly today. He leads. He restores. He prepares. The verbs are all His. The work is His. You are the sheep — small, often confused, easily distracted. He is the Shepherd — strong, patient, faithful, never lost. Let Him do the leading today.',
