        devotional: 'Hagar was a slave. Abused, pregnant, alone, fleeing in the wilderness. The angel of the Lord found her by a spring. He called her by name. He gave her a future. And Hagar — a foreign slave woman — became the FIRST PERSON IN THE BIBLE to name God. She called Him EL ROI: THE GOD WHO SEES ME.\n\nThat detail is staggering. The first one to name God was not a king, not a priest, not a prophet, not even an Israelite. It was an Egyptian slave who had been used and discarded. She looked into the face of the living God and gave Him a name. He let her keep it.\n\nWhere are you in your hidden corner today? The corner nobody at school knows about. The struggle nobody at work sees. The grief that is invisible to the people you live with. EL ROI is in your corner. He sees you. He sees the part you have not been able to put into words. The God who saw Hagar at the spring is in the room with you right now.',
