        keyVerse: { ref: 'Isaiah 40:28', text: 'Have you not known? Have you not heard? The LORD is the everlasting God, the Creator of the ends of the earth. He does not faint or grow weary; his understanding is unsearchable.' },
        devotional: 'EL OLAM means THE EVERLASTING GOD. Before time began. Through all of history. After time ends. He is unchanging, untiring, unwavering. He never gets old. He never gets weak. He never gets tired of you.\n\nIsaiah 40 makes the contrast painful and clear. EVEN YOUTHS shall faint and be weary. Even the most energetic, optimistic, can-do generation runs out of gas. EL OLAM does not. He is always at full strength. And — astonishingly — He shares that strength with those who wait on Him. "They shall mount up with wings like eagles."\n\nBefore the beginning. After the end. Present right now. The same God who has been Himself forever is the God who is paying attention to the small details of your Tuesday. He does not run out. He does not check the time. He does not have anywhere else to be. Rest in His EL OLAM-ness today.',
