        devotional: 'Isaiah saw the Lord on a throne, high and lifted up. The seraphim cried "HOLY, HOLY, HOLY" — three times, because Hebrew has no superlative form and triple repetition is the highest emphasis the language allows. God is not just holy. He is the HOLIEST. So other you cannot stand in His presence without being undone.\n\nIsaiah\'s response was the only honest one. "Woe is me! I am a man of unclean lips, and I dwell in the midst of a people of unclean lips!" Holiness reveals impurity. You cannot look at the sun and not notice the dust on your sleeve.\n\nBut then a seraph brought a burning coal from the altar and touched it to Isaiah\'s lips. "Your guilt is taken away. Your sin atoned for." Holiness does not just expose. It also CLEANSES. The Holy One who terrified Isaiah is the same Holy One who gently sent a coal to make him clean. He calls you near. Astoundingly. By design.',
