        devotional: 'Jesus made seven great "I AM" statements in John\'s Gospel. The first published one — "I AM the LIGHT of the WORLD" — was spoken at the Feast of Tabernacles, in the temple court that featured giant candelabras lit during the festival. The light blazing in the courtyard was meant to remember the pillar of fire that led Israel through the wilderness. Jesus, standing there, claimed to BE that pillar.\n\nLight reveals what darkness hides. Light makes the path visible. Light removes the fear of what might be lurking. Jesus is all of that for the human soul. He shows what darkness was concealing in you. He makes the next step visible. He removes the dread of the unknown future. The room you live in is bright because He is in it.\n\nWhat dark room in your life is He inviting Himself into? The shame closet. The chapter of the past you have not let Him touch. The future you have been afraid to look at. Flip the light on. Whatever is in there belongs to the Light of the World now.',
