        devotional: 'After feeding the 5,000, Jesus claimed something audacious: I AM the BREAD of LIFE. Not "I make bread." Not "I bless your bread." I AM bread. Daily, substantive, nourishing — the kind of food you need every morning, not as decoration but as substance.\n\nMost Christians treat Jesus like a SEASONING — a sprinkle of religion on top of an otherwise self-sustaining life. He says no. He is the bread itself. The protein. The carbs. The thing your soul actually needs to function. Try to live on Jesus-as-seasoning and you will starve spiritually no matter how impressive your career resume is.\n\nDaily bread. Not weekly bread. Not Sunday-only bread. The same way you cannot eat for the week on Sunday morning, your soul cannot run on a once-a-week service. Open the Word today. Pray. Be present to the Bread of Life. Hunger and thirst evaporate where He is the actual menu.',
