        keyVerse: { ref: 'John 7:37-38', text: 'If anyone thirsts, let him come to me and drink. Whoever believes in me, as the Scripture has said, "Out of his heart will flow rivers of living water."' },
        devotional: 'Jesus told the Samaritan woman at the well: "If you knew the gift of God, and who it is that is saying to you ‘give me a drink\' — you would have asked HIM, and he would have given you LIVING WATER." Living water in the ancient world meant SPRING water — water that bubbles up, fresh and moving, as opposed to STAGNANT water collected in a cistern.\n\nThat is the difference Jesus makes. Religion fills a cistern. Christianity has a spring. Religion gives you rules to follow and quickly stagnates into duty. Jesus gives you a SOURCE of life inside you that keeps producing freshness, even when external circumstances are dry.\n\nThe water is not for hoarding. John 7 says rivers flow OUT of the heart of the believer. The living water is for you, but it does not stop with you. It refreshes the people around you. The Spirit inside you is meant to overflow. Drink today. Then let it flow.',
