        devotional: 'Jesus said "I AM THE TRUE VINE" the night before His crucifixion. Israel had often been called a "vine" in the Old Testament — and Israel had usually disappointed. Jesus claims to be the TRUE vine, the one that finally bears the fruit Israel was meant to bear. And the branches — that is YOU.\n\nFruit comes from CONNECTION, not effort. A branch that tries hard to grow grapes apart from the vine produces nothing no matter how dedicated. ABIDE — meaning stay attached, stay present, stay in relationship with the vine — and the sap does its work over time. Without Him: nothing. With Him: much fruit.\n\nMost Christians try to MANUFACTURE the fruit by force. They strain. They strive. They burn out. The instruction is much gentler. ABIDE. Stay close. Stay attached. Stay in the conversation. The fruit will come — not because of your strain, but because of His sap.',
