        devotional: 'Three claims in one sentence — and any one of them is enough to make every other religion uncomfortable. Jesus says He is THE WAY. THE TRUTH. THE LIFE. Not a way among many. Not a teacher of truth. Not a source of life. THE singular, definitive, exclusive Way, Truth, and Life.\n\nThen He closes with the kicker: NO ONE comes to the Father except through Me. That sentence is the offense of Christianity to a pluralistic culture. Jesus is not one of several paths up the mountain. He is the mountain. He is the path. He is the destination. He is everything that matters in the project of being reconciled to God.\n\nThe sentence is exclusive but also wonderfully inclusive. EVERYONE who comes to Him gets to the Father. No nationality, language, age, race, or background bars the way. The exclusivity is about the path, not the people. He is open to all who come THROUGH HIM. Today, come.',
